  "tcmTraditionalUsage": {
    "en": "Changpu is an acrid, warm herb that enters the heart and stomach meridians. It opens the orifices, vaporises phlegm, transforms turbid dampness and pacifies the spirit. It can also benefit the throat, and is used to treat a hoarse voice due to laryngitis or inflamed vocal chords. Changpu removes obstructions caused by phlegm and opens the sensory orifices, sharpening cognitive functions and treating forgetfulness, tinnitus, dizziness and insomnia.\n",
    "zh-Hant": "菖蒲亦即石菖蒲，屬於開竅藥，藥味辛而苦，藥性溫，歸於心、胃、肝經，能豁痰開竅、袪濕寧神、醒脾開胃，常用於痰濕蒙蔽清竅的神昏不清。\n",
    "zh-Hans": "菖蒲亦即石菖蒲，属于开竅药，药味辛而苦，药性溫，歸于心、胃、肝经，能豁痰开竅、袪湿寧神、醒脾开胃，常用于痰湿蒙蔽清竅的神昏不清。\n"
  },
